User Registration API Call Flow
Client sends a POST request to /api/v1/users/register with username, password, and email in the JSON body.
app.js receives the request and forwards it to the user routes using app.use("/api/v1/users", userRoutes).
user.route.js matches the /register endpoint and calls the registerUser controller function.
user.controller.js (registerUser) handles:
Validating input data.
Checking if the username or email already exists using the User model.
Creating and saving a new user if validation passes.
Sending a success or error response.
user.model.js defines the schema and interacts with MongoDB to store user data.

http://localhost:5000/api/v1/users/register

